---
import Layout from '../../layouts/PhotosSaverLayout.astro'

const title = 'Terms of Service - Photos Saver'
const description =
  'Terms of Service for Photos Saver, a Google Photos companion app by Anas Alqoyyum.'
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
    <header class="border-b border-stone-200 pb-5 dark:border-zinc-800">
      <h1
        class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
      >
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-6 text-stone-600 dark:text-zinc-400">
        Last updated: March 17, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div
      class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-[15px] leading-7 text-stone-700 dark:text-zinc-300"
    >
      <section class="space-y-3">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service govern your use of Photos Saver, a browser
          extension and backend service operated by Anas Alqoyyum. By using
          Photos Saver, you agree to these terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Use of the service
        </h2>
        <ul
          class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 marker:text-stone-400 dark:marker:text-zinc-600"
        >
          <li>
            You may use Photos Saver only in compliance with applicable law and
            platform rules.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for the images, pages, and Google account
            content you choose to access or upload.
          </li>
          <li>
            You must have the necessary rights and permissions for content you
            save through the service.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Google services
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos Saver depends on Google APIs and Google Photos. Your use of
          those services remains subject to Google's own terms, policies, and
          technical limitations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Availability
        </h2>
        <p>
          Photos Saver is provided on an as-is and as-available basis. Features
          may change, pause, or stop without notice, including when required by
          security, maintenance, provider policy, or platform changes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          No warranty
        </h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, Photos Saver is provided
          without warranties of any kind, express or implied, including
          warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, and
          non-infringement.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Limitation of liability
        </h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, Anas Alqoyyum will not be
          liable for indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive
          damages, or for any loss of data, business, profits, or access arising
          from your use of Photos Saver.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Termination
        </h2>
        <p>
          Access to Photos Saver may be suspended or terminated at any time,
          especially in cases of misuse, abuse, security concerns, or required
          policy compliance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-3">
        <h2
          class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-stone-950 dark:text-zinc-50"
        >
          Contact
        </h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms, use the public contact links listed
          in the footer of this page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
